episodes.title: It's Worse Than I Thought
He Cheated 3 Times (that I know of)
What Really Ended Our Scientology Marriage
episodes.description:
In this video, I share the story of my marriage inside Scientology, from the strict rules and pressures of the Sea Org to how the cult’s control shaped our relationship. My ex-husband and I discuss our unique experiences, the impact of Scientology’s influence on our lives, and the real reason we eventually divorced long after leaving. We also reflect on our relationship after divorce, how we’ve rebuilt our lives outside of Scientology, and what it means to find healing and friendship after everything we’ve been through.

Orange, Coconut & Walnut Granola
8 cups oats
2 tsp cinnamon
2 tsp sea salt
Zest of one orange
2 tsp vanilla extract
1 cup maple syrup
1 cup olive oil
3 cups walnuts
2 cups unsweetened shredded coconut
Instructions:

Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). In a large bowl, mix together the oats, cinnamon, sea salt, orange zest, and 2 cups of unsweetened shredded coconut. In a separate bowl, whisk the vanilla extract, maple syrup, and olive oil until combined. Pour the wet ingredients over the dry mixture and stir well to coat everything evenly. Add the walnuts and give it another good mix. Spread the granola in an even layer on a large baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Bake for 25 minutes, stirring halfway through to ensure even toasting. Once done, remove from the oven and allow the granola to cool completely before transferring to an airtight container.

Toll House Chocolate Chip Cookies
2 ¼ cups all-purpose flour
1 tsp baking soda
1 tsp salt
1 cup (2 sticks) butter, softened
¾ cup granulated sugar
¾ cup packed brown sugar
1 tsp vanilla extract
2 large eggs
2 cups (12 oz package) semi-sweet chocolate chips
1 cup chopped nuts (optional)
Instructions:

Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C). In a small bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, and salt. In a large bowl, beat the softened butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar, and vanilla extract until creamy. Add the eggs one at a time. Gradually add the flour mixture and mix until combined. Stir in the chocolate chips and nuts, if using. Drop rounded tablespoons of dough onto baking sheets. Bake for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.

Roasted Cherry Tomato and Coconut Milk Soup
Ingredients:
2 pints cherry tomatoes
1 head garlic (whole)
1 yellow onion, roughly chopped
1 bunch fresh basil
1 bunch fresh thyme
Pinch of red pepper flakes
Salt and pepper, to taste
Healthy drizzle of olive oil
½ cup vegetable broth
½ cup coconut milk
Instructions:
Preheat the oven to 480°F (250°C).
Spread the cherry tomatoes, whole garlic head (with the top sliced off), and chopped onion on a baking sheet.
Add the basil and thyme sprigs to the pan, then drizzle everything with olive oil and sprinkle with red pepper flakes, salt, and pepper. Mix until everything is well coated.
Roast for 25-35 minutes, or until the tomatoes are soft and slightly blistered, and the garlic is tender.
Squeeze the roasted garlic out of the skins into a blender.
Add the roasted tomatoes, onions, basil, thyme (remove the stems), and any pan juices.
Pour in the vegetable broth and coconut milk, and blend until smooth.
Transfer the blended soup to a pot and heat gently over medium heat until warmed through.
Taste and adjust seasoning with salt and pepper if needed.
Serve hot, garnished with fresh basil and a little crème fraîche if you have it.
